      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "\"Quiet confidence\" is a Western bias, and expecting everyone to conform to it is limiting. While some cultures value directness, others prioritize harmony and indirect communication, which are equally valid high-level traits. The key is not to force one style, but to be acutely aware of the local communication norms. If you are in a culture where deference to seniority is paramount, showing that respect is far more professional than trying to dominate the conversation.",
